<p>
<p>A and B are two events in a chance experiment. The following probabilities are given: P(A) = 0.30, P(B) = 0.40, P(A or B) = 0.58. Which of the following statements is correct?</p>
</p>]]></text>
</questiontext>
<generalfeedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
</p>]]></text>
